WHAT YOU WILL FIND HERE
-----------------------

The development version of Waf (1.6)

For the manual: http://freehackers.org/~tnagy/wafbook160p2/index.html
For the api docs: http://freehackers.org/~tnagy/wafdoc160p2/index.html
For the examples: see the folder demos/

HOW TO CREATE THE WAF SCRIPT
----------------------------

Python 2.6, 2.7, 3.0 or 3.1 is required to generate the waf script.
Just execute:
$ ./waf-light configure build
Or, if you have several python versions installed:
$ python3 ./waf-light configure build

HOW TO TRY THE EXAMPLES
-----------------------

Try this:
$ cp waf demos/c/
$ cd demos/c/
$ ./waf configure build

API DOCS
--------

Use this command:
epydoc -v -o wafdoc160p2 --name epydoc --css white waflib/

